how many nursing home housekeepers out there we deserve some respect i work at a local nursing home as a housekeeper our administrative staff is so rude along with the rest of the staff they expect us to do work that is not in our job description for example picking up trash that they throw down on purpose leaving bm diapers in the floor and saying things like oh thats ok the housekeeper will get it we already do part of the cna's job also patient escort and make sure they are turned every few hours reporting abuse and neglect falls and are expected to clean up spills that the cna's do or it will be there all day we get treated like we are no one but can you imagine what the place would look like if not for us our job is as important as theirs why do they look down on us you are not working in a good place i have worked in nursing homes and i am thankful for the housekeepers maybe apply somewhere else your job is just as important as anyone elses and you deserve respect a true professional doesnt look down on others we are all team members working for the best outcome Social rule Certified Nursing Assistant Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Palliative care Theory of conduct Dialysis Nursing home Division of labour Florence Nightingale Nurse 1957 World Series Infantilism Professional wrestling match types Baseball Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity 2005 Belgian Grand Prix 2005 trial of Michael Jackson July 2005 in Malaysia and Singapore Housekeeper (servant) Stroke Nursing Good Times Ethics Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans National Kidney Foundation Singapore Plame affair Care Bears Paralegal National Health Service Economic inequality Child abuse Pittsburgh Steelers August 2005 in Malaysia and Singapore Drug abuse Eddie Guerrero New York Jets Summa Theologiae Goodness and value theory Abu Ghraib torture and prisoner abuse Dead Like Me Urinary incontinence September 2005 in Malaysia and Singapore Canasta Similarities betw